Watchmoor Park is a fully managed business park located in Camberley, minutes from the M3 and just 33 miles from Central London.Â Smarter Spaces are a selection of individual offices that are available immediately on either a short or long term agreement.
They start from 500 sq ft and range up to 5,000 sq ft (5-100 people).

Building 9 at Watchmoor Park presents a first floor, open plan office space across two wings connected via a double height atrium providing plenty of natural light.Â 

Watchmoor Park is nestled amongst the green surroundings of Camberley, while offering excellent connectivity and a number of travel options via road and rail, making it easy for you and your employees to get there and away. With Central London 33 miles away and Farnborough Rail Station just an 8 minute drive, this is what better connected space looks like.

Building 1 occupies a prominent position at the entrance of Watchmoor Park. Watchmoor Park is situated just off the A331. The property is a two storey headquarters building totaling 56,780 sq. ft. with approximately 12,000 sq. ft. laboratory space on the ground floor.

Camberley is located approximately 30 miles southwest of Central London and benefits from excellent communications with direct access via the A331 to the M3 (Junction 4). Farnborough Station is a short eight-minute drive from the park providing direct train links to London Waterloo in 45 minutes. Heathrow Airport is approximately 18 miles northwest of Watchmoor Park. Local amenities include three large superstores; Sainsburys, a short walk from the Park, M&S and Tesco. Major occupiers on the park include; Herrington Carmichael, Jenoptik, Jagermeister, Places Leisure, Novartis, Bachy
Soletanche, and Creative Food Europe.
